aa(lp183
VAnd again, I felt kind of uncomfortable with the notion
p184
aVthat a building the size of the Washington building \u2014
p185
aV50,000 square feet \u2014 will sit on that fragile hill
p186
aVand that we will go into galleries \u2014 rooms with doors
p187
aVand sort of familiar rooms \u2014 to tell the story of the Holocaust.
p188
aVAnd I proposed that we cut through the mountain. That was my first sketch.
p189
aVJust cut the whole museum through the mountain \u2014
p190
aVenter from one side of the mountain,
p191
aVcome out on the other side of the mountain \u2014
p192
aVand then bring light through the mountain into the chambers.
